    "Malik et al. (2023) pointed out its limitations, noting deficiencies in common sense reasoning tasks and raising concerns about its language coverage (Bang et al., 2023).",
    "Previous research has indicated that AI-powered chatbots offer a wide array of advantages in the field of education (Kooli, 2023; Mohamed, 2023).",
    "These chatbots enable students to access information from diverse sources and at various times, provide personalised assistance by recalling past interactions, and offer prompt feedback that simulates human interaction (Chen et al., 2023; Ilieva et al., 2023).",
    "Furthermore, owing to their unique capabilities, chatbots empower students to manage their knowledge and effectively perform educational tasks (Al-Sharafi et al., 2022).",
    "A growing body of research has examined the perception of university and on the use of ChatGPT in academia (Firat, 2023; Singh et al., 2023)."
